&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Midwives - Band 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Surrey Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is recruiting enthusiastic, innovative Band 5 Midwives to join their team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Midwives who are able to meet the challenge of delivering high standards of care and are ensuring that each woman’s journey to motherhood is an individualised experience. The candidate must be willing and able to work both in the hospital and community setting and as part of a continuity of carer team ensuring that women receive the BEST care available during their pregnancy and post natal period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must hold NMC midwifery registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to be able to show evidence of current practice/updating.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please contact Matrons Tanya Ashton or Katy Lucas for further information or you may wish to arrange an informal visit on 01483 571122 extension 2068/4708&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
